title: Michelle Kwan
summary: Michelle Wingshan Kwan[2] (born July 7, 1980) is an American retired figure skater. She is a two-time Olympic medalist (silver in 1998, bronze in 2002), a five-time World champion (1996, 1998, 2000, 2001, 2003) and a nine-time U.S. champion (1996, 1998â€“2005). She is tied with Maribel Vinson for the all-time National Championship record.
